Section 3:
Section 2-106.3. A. Subject to the availability of funding,
22
the Department of Public Safety shall establish a Fraudulent
23
Documents Identification (FDI) Unit an Identity Verification Unit
24
Req. No. 10690 Page 1
1 (IVU ) for the primary purpose of investigating and apprehending
2 persons or entities that participate in the sale or distribution of
3 fraudulent documents used for identification purposes. The unit
4 shall additionally specialize in fraudulent identification documents
5 created and prepared for persons who are unlawfully residing within
6 the State of Oklahoma. The Department shall employ sufficient
7 employees to investigate and implement an FDI Unit IVU.
8 B. The Commissioner of Public Safety is hereby authorized to
9 adopt and enforce such rules as may be necessary for operation of
10 the IVU and to carry out the power and duties assigned to the IVU by
11 this title.
12 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-110.2, as
13 amended by Section 51, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
14 Section 6-110.2), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 6-110.2. A. Service Oklahoma shall implement a
16 procedure for computerized finger imaging by means of an inkless
17 finger image scanning device and shall require every applicant for
18 an original, renewal or replacement driver license or identification
19 card to submit to finger imaging for the purposes of proof of
20 identity and to ensure the security of the driver license or
21 identification card issued to the applicant. If the finger image of
22 a person over sixty-five (65) years of age cannot be scanned and the
23 issuing agent can personally verify the individual's identity with
24 alternative identification, the finger imaging shall be overridden.
Req. No. 10690 Page 2
1 Mean s must be provided to trace to the agent who authorized the
2 override.
3 B. No unemancipated person under eighteen (18) years of age
4 shall be issued a driver license or identification card by Service
5 Oklahoma unless an authorization form, prescribed and furnished by
6 Service Oklahoma, or notarized affidavit authorizing the finger
7 imaging of the person and signed by the legal custodial parent,
8 legal guardian, or legal custodian of the person, is in the
9 possession of Service Oklahoma.
10 C. No law enforcement agency of the state or federal government
11 other than Service Oklahoma the Department of Public Safety shall
12 have access to any information collected through the use of
13 computerized finger imaging without first obtaining a court order
14 from a judge of competent jurisdiction; provided, however, the
15 Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation shall have access to such
16 imaging for the purpose of identifying a person who is deceased,
17 missing or endangered. Each application for an order authorizing
18 the access to any information collected through the use of
19 computerized finger imaging shall be made in writing upon oath or
20 affirmation to a judge of competent jurisdiction. Each application
21 shall establish probable cause for belief that a named individual is
22 committing, has committed or is about to commit a particular
23 violation of law.
24
Req. No. 10690 Page 3
1 D. Service Oklahoma shall adopt rules as may be necessary to
2 carry out the provisions of this section.
3 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-301, as
4 amended by Section 76, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
5 Section 6-301), is amended to read as follows:
6 Section 6-301. It shall be unlawful for any person to commit
7 any of the acts specified in paragraph 1 or 2 of this section in
8 relation to an Oklahoma driver license or identification card
9 authorized to be issued by Service Oklahoma pursuant to the
10 provisions of Sections 6-101 through 6-309 of this title or any
11 driver license or other evidence of driving privilege or
12 identification card authorized to be issued by the state of origin.
13 1. It is a misdemeanor for any licensee:
14 a. to display or cause or permit to be displayed one's
15 own license after such license has been suspended,
16 revoked or canceled or to possess one's own license
17 after having received notice of its suspension,
18 revocation, or cancellation,
19 b. to lend one's own license or identification card to
20 any other person or knowingly permit the use thereof
21 by another,
22 c. to display or cause or permit to be displayed or to
23 possess a license or identification card issued to
24 oneself which bears altered information concerning the
Req. No. 10690 Page 4
1 date of birth, expiration date, sex, height, eye
2 color, weight or license or card number,
3 d. to fail or refuse to surrender to Service Oklahoma
4 upon its lawful demand any license or identification
5 card which has been suspended, revoked or canceled,
6 e. to permit any unlawful use of a license or
7 identification card issued to oneself,
8 f. to do any act forbidden or fail to perform any act
9 required by this chapter, excepting those acts as
10 provided in paragraph 2 of this section,
11 g. to display or represent as one's own, any license or
12 identification card not issued to such person, unless
13 under conditions provided in subparagraph e of
14 paragraph 2 of this section, or
15 h. to add to, delete from, alter, or deface the required
16 information on a driver license or identification
17 card.
18 2. It is a felony for any person:
19 a. to create, publish or otherwise manufacture an
20 Oklahoma or other state license or identification card
21 or facsimile thereof, or to create, manufacture or
22 possess an engraved plate or other such device, card,
23 laminate, digital image or file, or software for the
24 printing of an Oklahoma or other state license or
Req. No. 10690 Page 5
1 identification card or facsimile thereof, except as
2 authorized pursuant to this title,
3 b. to display or cause or permit to be displayed or to
4 knowingly possess any state counterfeit or fictitious
5 license or identification card,
6 c. to display or cause to be displayed or to knowingly
7 possess any state license or identification card
8 bearing a fictitious or forged name or signature,
9 d. to display or cause to be displayed or to knowingly
10 possess any state license or identification card
11 bearing the photograph of any person, other than the
12 person named thereon as licensee,
13 e. to display or represent as one's own, any license or
14 identification card not issued to him or her, for the
15 purpose of committing a fraud in any commercial
16 transaction or to mislead a peace officer in the
17 performance of his or her duties, or
18 f. to use a false or fictitious name in any application
19 for a license or identification card or to knowingly
20 make a false statement or to knowingly conceal a
21 material fact or otherwise commit a fraud in any such
22 application.
23 3. It is a felony for any employee or person authorized to
24 issue or approve the issuance of licenses or identification cards
Req. No. 10690 Page 6
1 unde r this title to knowingly issue or attempt to issue a license or
2 identification card or to knowingly give approval for, cause, or
3 attempt to cause a license or identification card to be issued:
4 a. to a person not entitled thereto,
5 b. bearing erroneous information thereon, or
6 c. bearing the photograph of a person other than the
7 person named thereon.
8 Such conduct shall be grounds for termination of employment of the
9 employee.
10 4. The violation of any of the provisions of paragraph 1 of
11 this section shall constitute a misdemeanor and shall, upon
12 conviction thereof, be punishable by a fine of not less than Twenty-
13 five Dollars ($25.00), nor more than Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00);
14 the violation of any of the provisions of paragraph 2 or 3 of this
15 section shall constitute a felony and shall, upon conviction
16 thereof, be punishable by a fine not exceeding Ten Thousand Dollars
17 ($10,000.00) or a term of imprisonment in the custody of the
18 Department of Corrections not to exceed seven (7) years, or by both
19 such fine and imprisonment.
20 5. Notwithstanding any provision of this section, Service
21 Oklahoma the Department of Public Safety, through its Identity
22 Verification Unit (IVU), may, upon the request of the chief
23 administrator of a law enforcement, military, or intelligence
24 agency, authorize the issuance to and display, and possession by a
Req. No. 10690 Page 7
1 pers on of a license which would otherwise be a violation of this
2 section, for the sole purpose of aiding in a criminal investigation
3 or a military or intelligence operation. While acting pursuant to
4 such authorization by Service Oklahoma the Department, such person
5 shall not be prosecuted for a violation under this section unless
6 the person exceeds the scope or duration of the Department's
7 authorization. Upon termination of such investigation or operation
8 or upon request, Service Oklahoma shall forthwith cause such license
9 to be returned to Service Oklahoma of the Department, the chief
10 administrator of the law enforcement agency requesting the issuance
11 of the license and the recipient of the license shall be jointly
12 responsible to ensure the license is promptly returned to the
13 Department. The Department and Service Oklahoma shall enter into
14 interagency agreements as may be necessary to fulfill the powers and
15 duties set forth in this subsection. The Department is authorized
16 to enter into interagency agreements with law enforcement agencies
17 requesting issuance of such a license setting forth the terms of the
18 authorization for use of the license, the terms for custody and
19 control of the license, and the terms for duration and revocation of
20 authorization to use or possess the license.
